  <title>Introduction to Stacks</title>

  <p>A stack is a set of instructions that can configure a container based on any Linux distribution,
   allowing you to add packages and modify settings. You can create a new stack 
   by defining a base Linux distribution, such as Arch Linux, and an optional list of packages. 
   With this stack, you can create one or more new subsystems based on it.</p>

  <p>Stacks are shareable and restoreable, so you can easily share them with your team. Vanilla OS 
  already has a set of preconfigured stacks to access all the major Linux distributions.</p>

  <p>You can create stacks for each use case, for example, one with all the tools and libraries
   useful for development in various domains like 3D applications, music production, and programming.</p>

